# .env.example — the template for local environment config.
#
# Copy to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in as the project grows. This
# establishes the "secrets live in .env, never in git" habit before there are any
# real secrets to keep. Nothing here is consumed by the code yet — it is the home
# for future values (e.g. WiFi credentials for on-device monitoring, a weather API
# key for the env-context layer).

# Examples (uncomment + set when the feature that needs it lands):
# SPROUT_WIFI_SSID=
# SPROUT_WIFI_PASSWORD=
# SPROUT_WEATHER_API_KEY=
